               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480228-name-1222" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480228-name-1222" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480228-name-1222" type="surname" value="HARRIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480228-name-1222" type="given" value="ELIZABETH"></interp>ELIZABETH HARRIS.</persName>
                  </hi> I am the wife of Maurice James Harris, of the Water<lb></lb>loo-road—he keeps an oyster-shop. On Monday evening, 31st Jan., between ten and eleven o'clock, I missed a plated dish from the shop window, which I had seen safe about ten—there was a broken pane in the window, which had a board against it—a person could get the dish by putting his band through there.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184802280179"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480228-name-1223" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480228-name-1223" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480228-name-1223" type="surname" value="BEDLIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480228-name-1223" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BEDLIN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, L</hi> 133.) On Monday, 31st Jan., about a quarter to eleven o'clock in the evening, I was on duty in the Waterloo-road, and saw the two prisoners together, walking backwards and forwards, in front of the shop—I saw Best put his hand through the broken square, take out some<lb></lb>thing which glittered, and pass it to Josling—they then ran away—I ran after them, and took Josling—I am quite sure Best is the other—I had seen them the night before, and took notice of them—I took Best on the 10th Feb., told him what for, and he said he knew nothing at all of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Best's Defence.</hi> My father can prove I was a-bed at the time; Joaling knows I am innocent.</p>
